Lister is a Dutch organisation who helps people with psychiatric or addiction problems. We took over the development of a key business application that provides reporting and KPI metrics from a rather complex database (600+ tables).

• Backend .NET + Entity Framework development;
• Database design (MS SQL);
• Development of MS SQL stored procedures;
• Documentation

The project delivered the integration of KBC Group group level Identity Management System (IDM) with K&H Bank Central User Administration System (CUA) and the integration of local access management systems of KBC Belgium and K&H Bank. This also included several interfaces between group level and local SAP HR and a global security role management application.
My responsibilities as Business Analyst / Project Manager were:
 • Business process analysis and writing Business Requirement Specification representing K&H Bank in the project as Business Analyst in the pre-study phase;
 • Design the integration between group level IDM and K&H Bank CUA systems;
 • Writing implementation specification for the developers;
 • Development lead (Java, Perl);
 • User acceptance testing;
 • Documentation.

I represented K&H Bank as a Business Analyst in a pre-study on user administration requester tool replacement. KBC Group wanted to assess the costs and benefits of replacing the request tool of K&H CUA to the group standard HP Service Desk integrated requester tool.
My responsibilities as Business Analyst were:
•	Detailed presentation of K&H CUA;
•	Understanding the group level requester tool;
•	Mapping existing business processes and functionality to the group level solution;
•	Involved in writing the assessment report.

K&H Bank needed a new Central User Administration (CUA) system. It was based on BMC Software Identity Management Suite with higher level business processes and IT governance features implemented in and a custom built Java workflow application.

My duties and responsibilities as Business Analyst were:
 • Business process analysis;
 • Writing Business Requirement Specification for the subcontractor;
 • Involved in designing the new identity management solution;
 • Negotiating and designing workarounds with the client and the subcontractor;
 • Involved in development as well (Perl, Java, Shell);
 • User acceptance testing;
 • Documentation
